00:41:58.275 --> 00:42:00.400
So I have three kids,
they're all in their 20s now.

00:42:00.400 --> 00:42:02.020
So they're all millennials.

00:42:02.020 --> 00:42:06.610
So I speak a little millennial.

00:42:06.610 --> 00:42:07.480
Here's what I think.

00:42:07.480 --> 00:42:09.622
I think millennials are
just like our parents

00:42:09.622 --> 00:42:11.830
and our grandparents and
our great great grandparents

00:42:11.830 --> 00:42:14.680
in terms of their
genetic wiring and what

00:42:14.680 --> 00:42:16.390
they want as human beings.

00:42:16.390 --> 00:42:19.300
What I think has changed
is that the ability

00:42:19.300 --> 00:42:23.290
to say this job isn't
worth being treated badly

00:42:23.290 --> 00:42:24.187
has changed.

00:42:24.187 --> 00:42:26.020
In the United States,
when I was growing up,

00:42:26.020 --> 00:42:28.670
the average new house
was 1,500 square feet.

00:42:28.670 --> 00:42:31.700
The average new house size
today is 2,500 square feet.

00:42:31.700 --> 00:42:35.350
The average family size in
household went from 2.5 to 1.5.

00:42:35.350 --> 00:42:38.080
I grew up in a family of four.

00:42:38.080 --> 00:42:40.510
I couldn't wait to
get out of there.

00:42:40.510 --> 00:42:43.540
Now it's changed a little bit.

00:42:43.540 --> 00:42:49.480
So I would have put up
with any amount of pain

00:42:49.480 --> 00:42:52.920
to be gone and be out on my own.

00:42:52.920 --> 00:42:55.330
Now it's different, because
there's not so much pain back

00:42:55.330 --> 00:42:57.790
home, which I think is awesome.

00:42:57.790 --> 00:43:01.040
So my deal is the way that
millennials are saying,

00:43:01.040 --> 00:43:03.824
